programme.title: Lady Gaga
programme.desc: Lady Gaga's performance at the iTunes Festival in London on September 1, 2013 marks the superstar's first full concert since the The Born This Way Ball. It is an eight song set containing the world premiere of seven tracks from her fourth album, ARTPOP: "Aura" "MANiCURE" "Artpop" "Jewels N' Drugs" ft. T.I., Too $hort and Twista "Sexxx Dreams", "Swine" and "I Wanna Be With You", a song that transformed into "Dope" for ARTPOP. During the concert, captured stunningly in HD, Gaga says that she's "a bit like Dorothy right now." The stage is her Kansas, the crowd is her family, and their reunion is pure magic. Lady Gaga, her dancers, and her band traverse through visual and musical themes of love, sex, violence, beauty, danger, empowerment, hustle, lust, and above all ART. Throughout, Gaga lays her heart bare for the audience and the cameras with every note sung and every word spoken.

programme.title: Tuva Semmingsen, Jihye Kim, Johan Karlström & Christine Nonbo Andersen
programme.sub-title: Fantasymphony - One Concert to Rule Them All
programme.desc: The Danish National Symphony Orchestra opens the door to a wealth of fantasy universes in this mesmerizing concert program. Under the direction of German conductor Christian Schumann, the Danish National Symphony Orchestra, Danish National Concert Choir, and Danish National Junior Choir team up to perform music from the most popular fantasy movies, TV series and video games, including The Lord of the Rings, Harry Potter, Highlander, and The Chronicles of Narnia. Featured soloists in this concert are Danish soprano Christine Nonbo Andersen, Korean percussionist Jihye Kim, Norwegian mezzo-soprano Tuva Semmingsen, Swedish bass Johan Karlström, and British actor David Bateson. This performance was recorded at the DR Koncerthuset in Copenhagen, Denmark, in June 2019.

programme.title: Leonard Slatkin, Leonard Slatkin, Orchestre National de Lyon & Baiba Skride
programme.desc: Leonard Slatkin conducts the Orchestre national de Lyon in a concert recorded at the Auditorium de Lyon in France, 2013. The concert is a tribute to the organ of the Maurice-Ravel Auditorium, which was made by Aristide Cavaillé-Coll. The program features three works which premiered on exactly the same organ: Camille Saint-Saëns' Cyprès et Lauriers and Symphony No. 3 and Poulenc's Concerto for Organ, Timpani and Strings. Soloist is Vincent Warnier.

programme.title: Ballet of the Mariinsky Theatre
programme.desc: The Mariinsky Ballet performs 'Anna Karenina', a sweeping two-act ballet choreographed by Alexei Ratmansky. The ballet is based on Lev Tolstoy's 1877 novel that tells the tragic story of the married socialite Anna Karenina and her affair with cavalry officer Count Vronsky. The ballet opens where the novel ends: tormented by despair and loneliness, Anna throws herself under a train, whereupon Count Vronsky discovers his lover's lifeless body. Ratmansky's choreography is set to Rodion Shchedrin's music, which is performed by the Mariinsky Orchestra under the baton of Valery Gergiev. Among the dancers are Ulyana Lopatkina, Victor Baranov, Andrei Yermakov, and Svetlana Ivanova. This performance was recorded at the Mariinsky Theatre in St. Petersburg, Russia, in March 2014.

programme.title: Nikolay Lugansky & Vadim Rudenko
programme.sub-title: Piano Duets - Mozart, Ravel, Rachmaninoff a. o.
programme.desc: In this splendid concert, exceptional Russian pianists Nikolay Lugansky and Vadim Rudenko join forces in a program for two pianos comprising works of Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart, Maurice Ravel, Anton Arensky, Sergei Rachmaninoff, and Nikolai Kapustin. Both pianists, laureates of the prestigious International Tchaikovsky Competition in 1994, have received international recognition. They perform regularly in a duo. On the program: Mozart's Sonata for two pianos in D major, K. 448/375 A Ravel's La Valse (arr. for two pianos) Arensky's Suite No. 1 for two pianos, Op. 15 and Rachmaninoff's Suite No. 1 (Fantasy) for two pianos, Op. 5. As an encore, the duo performs ‘Romance' from Rachmaninoff's Suite No. 2 for two pianos, Op. 17, followed by ‘Overture' from Nikolai Kapustin's Sinfonietta, Op. 49. This performance was recorded at the Tchaikovsky Concert Hall in Moscow, Russia, on November 25, 2021.

programme.title: Die Flippers
programme.desc: Die Flippers machen sich auf in die Schweiz und dort in den malerischen Kanton Tessin. Wie kein anderer Landstrich vereint er einen Hauch "Bella Italia" mit der eindrucksvollen Landschaft der Alpen. Kein Wunder, dass er eines der beliebtesten Ferienziele in Europa ist. Mit im Gepäck hat das Hittrio Klassiker wie "Lass uns heute romantisch sein", "Der alte Maurice" und natürlich "Lago Maggiore".

programme.title: Bei Hübner
programme.desc: Uwe Hübner hat die Münchener Freiheit zu Gast im GoldStar-TV-Studio. Besonders ausführlich spricht er mit den Gründungsmitgliedern Stefan Zauner und Aron Strobel, die Einges über die Erfolgsgeschichte und die größten Hits der Band zu erzählen haben.

programme.title: Peter Kraus LIVE
programme.desc: Sein Hüftschwung ist so legendär wie der von Elvis. Und als Sänger, Gitarrist und Gelegenheitsschauspieler war Peter Kraus einer der ersten deutschsprachigen Künstler, die den Rock'n'Roll im Nachkriegsdeutschland salonfähig machten - mit Songs wie 'Susi Rock', 'Sugar Baby' oder 'Schwarze Rose Rosemarie'.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute zu Gast in Bad Waltersdorf
programme.desc: Inmitten des oststeirischen Hügellandes, genauer gesagt in der Thermenregion Bad Waltersdorf, heißt Dagmar Obernosterer ihre Gäste willkommen. Diese Sendung steht ganz im Zeichen von heißen Quellen, romantischen Herbstlandschaften und hochkarätigen Stars. Mit dabei sind auch die Lokalmatadore aus der Steiermark, die Stoakogler. 1968 begann die Gruppe ihre musikalische Laufbahn und nach 43 Jahren Bühne haben sie 2011 ihre Karriere beendet. Sie präsentieren ein Medley ihrer erfolgreichsten Hits.

programme.title: Bei Hübner
programme.desc: 1982 fing alles an: Nicole gewann mit dem Titel "Ein bisschen Frieden" den Grand Prix Eurovision de la Chanson in Harrogate/England. Über Nacht ist sie ein Star und das mit gerade mal 18 Jahren! "Bei Hübner“ spricht die erfolgreiche Sängerin ganz privat über Meilensteine ihrer Karriere, ihre große Liebe, ihre geheimen Ängste, Hoffnungen und Träume.

programme.title: Bei Hübner
programme.desc: Er war der „Junge mit der Mundharmonika“, denn gleich sein erster, war auch sein größter Hit: Bernd Clüver. GoldStar TV erinnert an den beliebten Sänger, der 2011 bei einem Treppensturz in seiner Wahlheimat Mallorca ums Leben kam. "Bei Hübner" spricht Bernd Clüver nicht nur über sein Leben auf der Bühne, sondern auch über Privates

programme.title: ZDF-Hitparade 3

programme.title: WILDES ÜBERLEBEN
programme.desc: Auch wenn Tiere scheinbar unmöglichen Chancen gegenüberstehen, können sie ihren Kampf ums Überleben gewinnen.Betreten Sie die Welt der nachtaktiven Tiere ... Ein Leben in der Nacht kann extreme Herausforderungen mit sich bringen – und enorme Chancen. In dieser Welt ohne Licht lauert Gefahr hinter jeder Ecke. Diese Episode entführt uns in eine Welt, die wir kaum sehen können – aber für viele Tiere ist das alles, was sie kennen. Primaten wie Eulen, Hyänen mit Supersinnen und leuchtende Insekten haben sich entwickelt, um in dieser Welt ohne Licht erfolgreich zu sein. Ob es um die Nahrungssuche, die Partnersuche oder den Kampf gegen Raubtiere geht, in dieser düsteren Welt werden nur die Stärksten – und Klügsten – überleben. Im Dschungel Madagaskars kommuniziert ein geheimnisvoller Verwandter des Igels über Geräusche, die von seinen Stacheln erzeugt werden. In den staubigen Ebenen des südlichen Afrikas wehrt ein wildes Honigdachs-Trio eine gefräßige Hyäne ab. Tief in einer Höhle in einem abgelegenen Teil Neuseelands erzeugen Millionen winziger Insekten eine unterirdische Lichtshow. Und an der Küste Chiles verlässt eine Fledermaus ihren Schlafplatz. Es ist Zeit zu essen – und es ernährt sich nur von Blut ... Dies sind nur einige der Arten, die in der dritten Folge vorgestellt werden. Als die Dunkelheit hereinbricht, haben diese nachtaktiven Tiere ihren eigenen Platz in einer Welt ohne Licht gefunden. Sie haben sich an das Leben im Dunkeln angepasst, von der Partnersuche bis zur Bewältigung der größten Herausforderungen des Lebens haben diese Kreaturen einige außergewöhnliche Fähigkeiten entwickelt.Sie haben ihren eigenen Weg gefunden, zu überleben – und zu gedeihen –, wenn die Sonne untergeht

programme.title: WILDES ÜBERLEBEN
programme.desc: Lernen Sie die Lebewesen kennen, die auf einzigartige Weise an das Leben in der Tiefkühltruhe angepasst sind. Tiere haben sich so entwickelt, dass sie in jedem Winkel des Planeten leben – aber keines ist so widerstandsfähig wie diejenigen, die in den kältesten Gefilden leben. Wir werden die überraschenden Anpassungen enthüllen, die die Lebewesen des kalten Wetters auf der Erde entwickelt haben, um zu überleben. Diese Episode führt uns in Länder mit eisigen Temperaturen, knapper Nahrung und kürzeren Tageslichtstunden. Das Gedeihen inmitten von Eis und Schnee ist eine der extremen Herausforderungen der Natur. An der Südspitze Chiles folgen wir einem verlorenen Puma, der im Schneesturm nach seiner Mutter sucht. In Finnland sucht ein Braunbär verzweifelt nach seiner letzten Mahlzeit, bevor er für den bevorstehenden langen, kalten Winter in den Winterschlaf geht. Im riesigen Nationalpark Yellowstone jagt ein Rudel Wölfe eine Herde Elche durch den tiefen Schnee. Und in den Karpaten Rumäniens nutzt ein Luchs sein unglaubliches Sehvermögen, um selbst die kleinste Beute aufzuspüren und zu töten. Für alle Tiere bringt der Winter einzigartige Herausforderungen mit sich. Aber die härtesten Lebewesen der Natur haben unglaubliche Möglichkeiten gefunden, in den kältesten Regionen unseres Planeten zu überleben. Ganz gleich, ob es darum geht, Nahrung zu finden, einen Partner zu beeindrucken oder dem schlimmsten Wetter aus dem Weg zu gehen, diese Tiere haben bemerkenswerte Anpassungen entwickelt, um die Kälte zu überlisten und im unerbittlichen Kampf ums Überleben erfolgreich zu sein.

Der Film zeigt die Kämpfe und Erfolge der Tiere, die auf diesen einzigartigen Inseln geboren, aufgezogen und geschützt werden.

programme.title: Curtis Stigers
programme.sub-title: Curtis Stigers - Fly Me To The Moon
programme.desc: The Danish Radio Big Band joins forces with American vocalist Curtis Stigers to celebrate Frank Sinatra's iconic concerts at The Sands Hotel in Las Vegas. Curtis Stigers and the big band present the most popular evergreens from the American songbook of the 1950s and 1960s, one of which is the classic that lend the concert its name: “Fly Me To The Moon”.

programme.title: Jazzmeia Horn
programme.desc: Vocalist Jazzmeia Horn's 2019 Malta Jazz Festival appearance was a celebration of jazz's future, infused with the soul of its past. Featuring Keith Brown (piano), Rashaan Carter (bass), Irwin Hall (flute and saxophone), and Anwar Marshall (drums), the young singer's performance was a reminder of jazz's enduring power to speak to the heart. Situated at the Valletta waterfront outside Our Lady of Liesse Church, Horn's concert was a truly spellbinding experience.

programme.title: Stochelo Rosenberg & Peter Beets
programme.desc: The treasured compositions of guitarist Django Reinhardt, the founding father of hot club jazz, are engraved in everyone's memory. Although Reinhardt missed two fingers of his left hand, his virtuoso technique was unrivalled. Dutch guitarist Stochelo Rosenberg and pianist Peter Beets now have the pleasure to bring Django's music back to life with their infectious improvisations.

programme.title: Wes Montgomery
programme.sub-title: Herbie Man & Sonny Sharrock - Memphis underground
programme.desc: This selection of unforgettable performances by some of the most iconic and influential jazz guitarists in history showcases these legends' unique essence. Revel in Wes Montgomery's virtuosity as he performs the captivating “Nica's Dream” in Holland in 1965, and delight in the expressive beauty of his rendition of “Here's That Rainy Day”, recorded in London in that same year. Experience the timeless appeal of Joe Pass's “You Stepped Out of a Dream” and “You Turned The Tables on Me”, recorded live in Hanover in 1975. The interplay between Jim Hall and Atilla Zoller borders on the impossible as they perform “Extensions” in Hanover in 1973. Enjoy Jim Hall's lyrical solo performance of “I'm Getting Sentimental Over You” from 1964. Witness Sonny Sharrock's avant-garde fusion of jazz and rock in an exhilarating performance of “Peanut", recorded live in France in 1970. Sharrock is joined by flutist Herbie Mann in a soulful performance of “Memphis Underground” from 1969. Immerse yourself in the magic of jazz guitar!

programme.title: Freddie Hubbard, Al Grey, Alvin Batiste & Al Casey
programme.sub-title: Freddie Hubbard & The Satchmo Legacy Live in 1987
programme.desc: Since 1977, Estival is a summer jazz festival in Switzerland, Lugano. Estival offers a thrilling and particularly surprising line-up that explores the rich world of contemporary music whilst promoting the understanding of different cultures, tolerance, and co-existence. This concert of Freddie Hubbard and the Satchmo Legacy in 1987, highlights the bebop legend's classic style and silky tone. Hubbard is an American jazz trumpeter whose unmistakable and influential tone contributed to new perspectives for modern jazz and bebop. He was also a well-known part of Art Blakey and the Jazz Messengers and is primarily known for playing bebop, hard bop, and post-bop styles from the early '60s onwards.

programme.title: Bootsy Collins
programme.sub-title: Casper the Funky Ghost: Bootsy Collins à Vienne
programme.desc: Bootsy Collins, famed for playing with George Clinton and his very own Rubber Band, is used to playing syncopated, hard and relentlessly rhythmic music. With this unique style Bootsy was a major influence on the development of funk. Now in his 60s, the bassist seems animated by a new energy that reflects his new work on the album ‘Tha Funk Capitol of the World'. With this album, Bootsy Collins pays tribute to the artists with whom he worked during his frantic career: from James Brown and Parliament-Funkadelic to Fatboy Slim. During this concert, recorded at the festival Jazz à Vienne, Bootsy maintains that same energy, giving a spectacular show.

programme.title: Christian Scott
programme.sub-title: Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah, The Walk
programme.desc: In 2019, the vibrant city of Sofia, Bulgaria, hosted the International A to JazZ Festival. Among the featured acts was the trailblazing jazz trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah. This genre-defying artist captivated the audience with his eclectic “stretch music” an approach that incorporates hip-hop and reaches back through the American canon into African percussion and its rich melodic content. Trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah's quintet, which includes drummer Corey Fonville, percussionist Weedie Braimah, pianist Lawrence Fields, and bass guitarist Max Mucha, delivered a performance that defied boundaries and expectations.

programme.title: Tony Bennett
programme.desc: Relive the magic of one of the most beloved crooners in music history in his prime: Tony Bennett! Recorded live in London's Royal Albert Hall on March 2, 1974, this enchanting performance showcases Bennett's remarkable vocal prowess and charisma to full effect. Bennett is accompanied by his musical director Torrie Zito and an orchestra of British musicians that includes Kenny Clare (drums), Don Lusher (trombone), and Kenny Baker (trumpet). Tune in for Bennett's captivating take on songs “The Good Things in Life”, “My Favorite Things”, “My Love”, “I've Got Five Dollars”, “It Don't Mean a Thing”, and “Maybe This Time” in this magical concert recording.

programme.title: Charles Mingus, Jaki Byard, Dannie Richmond & Johnny Coles
programme.sub-title: Charles Mingus And Eric Dolphy live in Liège
programme.desc: Charles Mingus showcases an exceptional concert performed in April 1965 featuring his most celebrated lineup: Jaki Byard (piano), Dannie Richmond (drums), Johnny Coles (trumpet), Clifford Jordan (tenor sax) and the great Eric Dolphy (alto sax, flute and bass clarinet). Recorded within an eight-day span, less than three months before Dolphy's death, the three concerts showcase Mingus's visionary leadership and the band's incredible depth and diversity with unique performances and arrangements of classics including ‘So Long Eric' and the groundbreaking ‘Meditations On Integration'.

programme.title: Lady Gaga
programme.desc: Lady Gaga's performance at the iTunes Festival in London on September 1, 2013 marks the superstar's first full concert since the The Born This Way Ball. It is an eight song set containing the world premiere of seven tracks from her fourth album, ARTPOP: "Aura" "MANiCURE" "Artpop" "Jewels N' Drugs" ft. T.I., Too $hort and Twista "Sexxx Dreams", "Swine" and "I Wanna Be With You", a song that transformed into "Dope" for ARTPOP. During the concert, captured stunningly in HD, Gaga says that she's "a bit like Dorothy right now." The stage is her Kansas, the crowd is her family, and their reunion is pure magic. Lady Gaga, her dancers, and her band traverse through visual and musical themes of love, sex, violence, beauty, danger, empowerment, hustle, lust, and above all ART. Throughout, Gaga lays her heart bare for the audience and the cameras with every note sung and every word spoken.

programme.title: Tuva Semmingsen, Jihye Kim, Johan Karlström & Christine Nonbo Andersen
programme.sub-title: Fantasymphony - One Concert to Rule Them All
programme.desc: The Danish National Symphony Orchestra opens the door to a wealth of fantasy universes in this mesmerizing concert program. Under the direction of German conductor Christian Schumann, the Danish National Symphony Orchestra, Danish National Concert Choir, and Danish National Junior Choir team up to perform music from the most popular fantasy movies, TV series and video games, including The Lord of the Rings, Harry Potter, Highlander, and The Chronicles of Narnia. Featured soloists in this concert are Danish soprano Christine Nonbo Andersen, Korean percussionist Jihye Kim, Norwegian mezzo-soprano Tuva Semmingsen, Swedish bass Johan Karlström, and British actor David Bateson. This performance was recorded at the DR Koncerthuset in Copenhagen, Denmark, in June 2019.

programme.title: Leonard Slatkin, Leonard Slatkin, Orchestre National de Lyon & Baiba Skride
programme.desc: Leonard Slatkin conducts the Orchestre national de Lyon in a concert recorded at the Auditorium de Lyon in France, 2013. The concert is a tribute to the organ of the Maurice-Ravel Auditorium, which was made by Aristide Cavaillé-Coll. The program features three works which premiered on exactly the same organ: Camille Saint-Saëns' Cyprès et Lauriers and Symphony No. 3 and Poulenc's Concerto for Organ, Timpani and Strings. Soloist is Vincent Warnier.

programme.title: Ballet of the Mariinsky Theatre
programme.desc: The Mariinsky Ballet performs 'Anna Karenina', a sweeping two-act ballet choreographed by Alexei Ratmansky. The ballet is based on Lev Tolstoy's 1877 novel that tells the tragic story of the married socialite Anna Karenina and her affair with cavalry officer Count Vronsky. The ballet opens where the novel ends: tormented by despair and loneliness, Anna throws herself under a train, whereupon Count Vronsky discovers his lover's lifeless body. Ratmansky's choreography is set to Rodion Shchedrin's music, which is performed by the Mariinsky Orchestra under the baton of Valery Gergiev. Among the dancers are Ulyana Lopatkina, Victor Baranov, Andrei Yermakov, and Svetlana Ivanova. This performance was recorded at the Mariinsky Theatre in St. Petersburg, Russia, in March 2014.

programme.title: Nikolay Lugansky & Vadim Rudenko
programme.sub-title: Piano Duets - Mozart, Ravel, Rachmaninoff a. o.
programme.desc: In this splendid concert, exceptional Russian pianists Nikolay Lugansky and Vadim Rudenko join forces in a program for two pianos comprising works of Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart, Maurice Ravel, Anton Arensky, Sergei Rachmaninoff, and Nikolai Kapustin. Both pianists, laureates of the prestigious International Tchaikovsky Competition in 1994, have received international recognition. They perform regularly in a duo. On the program: Mozart's Sonata for two pianos in D major, K. 448/375 A Ravel's La Valse (arr. for two pianos) Arensky's Suite No. 1 for two pianos, Op. 15 and Rachmaninoff's Suite No. 1 (Fantasy) for two pianos, Op. 5. As an encore, the duo performs ‘Romance' from Rachmaninoff's Suite No. 2 for two pianos, Op. 17, followed by ‘Overture' from Nikolai Kapustin's Sinfonietta, Op. 49. This performance was recorded at the Tchaikovsky Concert Hall in Moscow, Russia, on November 25, 2021.
